  "text": "In population screening machine learning methods are used to differentiate between benign and malignant lung nodules based on low-dose computed tomography , which is considered as a widespread standard in detecting and analysis of lung diseases. In case of expected tumors sampled it is possible to use technics on the basis of gene activity pattern in affected cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Thus gene expression levels can be used as classification attributes which characterize production rate of protein in lung tumor cells compared with healthy cells [CITATION_3] .",
